A Battle Between Two Former Colleagues for an Organization

Elon Musk, along with a group of investors, has made a $97.4 billion offer to acquire OpenAI. The proposal aims to bring OpenAI back to its original mission as a nonprofit organization focused on AI safety.

Sam Altman, the CEO of OpenAI, swiftly rejected the offer and responded on the social network X, saying, 'No, thanks, but if you'd like, we'll buy Twitter for $9.74 billion.'

Musk and Altman co-founded OpenAI as a nonprofit organization in 2015, but disagreements later arose between them.
